messages.speech:
Influenza (also known as flu) is a contagious respiratory illness caused by flu viruses. It can cause mild to severe illness, and at times can lead to death. Flu is different from a cold. 
Someone who is sick with flu often feel some or all of these symptoms: chills
Cough, Sore throat, Runny nose, body aches, Headaches, Fatigue (tiredness),Some people may have vomiting and diarrhea. Do you want to know about its preventive  measures?
